        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD sent Rivers a copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref> in January 1863 to thank him for his assistance with the chapter on bud-variation for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3918.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Thomas Rivers, 15 January [1863]</ref>). Rivers had first read <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref> several years earlier (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3933.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Thomas Rivers, 21 January 1863</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Some indication of the contents of the missing portion of the letter is given by the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3982.xml" resp="#automat" cert="medium">letter to Rivers of [14 February 1863]</ref>, in which CD thanked him for ‘capital’ information concerning inheritance in an ash tree and a species of thorn. CD made extensive use of this information in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 2: 18–19.</note>
